  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Access Token (OAuth 2.0)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "client_credentials",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{client_id}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{client_secret}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "scope",
                  "value": "payments:read customers:read refunds:read events:read merchants:read",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Space-separated scopes. Must be a subset of scopes assigned to your consumer."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/oauth/token",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "oauth",
                "token"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Obtain an OAuth 2.0 access token using the Client Credentials flow.\n\n**Request:**\n- `grant_type`: Must be `client_credentials`\n- `client_id`: Your registered client ID\n- `client_secret`: Your registered client secret\n- `scope` (optional): Space-separated list of scopes. Must be a subset of scopes assigned to your consumer.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJ...\",\n  \"token_type\": \"bearer\",\n  \"expires_in\": 3600,\n  \"scope\": \"payments:read customers:read refunds:read events:read merchants:read\"\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** This collection is configured to auto-manage tokens. You typically don't need to call this manually \u2014 Postman will automatically obtain and refresh the token."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                {
                  "key": "Content-Type",
                  "value": "application/json"
                }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n  \"token_type\": \"bearer\",\n  \"expires_in\": 3600,\n  \"scope\": \"payments:read customers:read refunds:read events:read merchants:read\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Invalid Credentials",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [
                {
                  "key": "Content-Type",
                  "value": "application/json"
                }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"invalid_client\",\n  \"message\": \"Invalid client_id or client_secret\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Consumer Suspended",
              "status": "Forbidden",
              "code": 403,
              "header": [
                {
                  "key": "Content-Type",
                  "value": "application/json"
                }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"access_denied\",\n  \"message\": \"Consumer is suspended\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
